verses.text_plain: God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble.
verses.verse_html:
1God is our refuge and strength, a very present help in trouble. ▼
▼ for: or, of

verses.text_plain: Therefore will not we fear, though the earth be removed, and though the mountains be carried into the midst of the sea;
verses.verse_html:
2Therefore will not we fear, though the earth be removed, and though the mountains be carried into the midst of the sea; ▼
▼ midst…: Heb. heart of the seas

footnotes.body_text: ▼ midst…: Heb. heart of the seas
footnotes.body_html: ▼ midst…: Heb. heart of the seas

verses.text_plain: Though the waters thereof roar and be troubled, though the mountains shake with the swelling thereof. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 3Though the waters thereof roar and be troubled, though the mountains shake with the swelling thereof. Selah.

verses.text_plain: There is a river, the streams whereof shall make glad the city of God, the holy place of the tabernacles of the most High.
verses.verse_html: 4There is a river, the streams whereof shall make glad the city of God, the holy place of the tabernacles of the most High.

verses.text_plain: God is in the midst of her; she shall not be moved: God shall help her, and that right early.
verses.verse_html:
5God is in the midst of her; she shall not be moved: God shall help her, and that right early. ▼
▼ and…: Heb. when the morning appeareth

tokens.text: of her; she shall not be moved

footnotes.body_text: ▼ and…: Heb. when the morning appeareth
footnotes.body_html: ▼ and…: Heb. when the morning appeareth

verses.text_plain: The heathen raged, the kingdoms were moved: he uttered his voice, the earth melted.
verses.verse_html: 6The heathen raged, the kingdoms were moved: he uttered his voice, the earth melted.

verses.text_plain: The Lord of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.
verses.verse_html:
7The Lord of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah. ▼
▼ our…: Heb. an high place for us

footnotes.body_text: ▼ our…: Heb. an high place for us
footnotes.body_html: ▼ our…: Heb. an high place for us

verses.text_plain: Come, behold the works of the Lord, what desolations he hath made in the earth.
verses.verse_html: 8Come, behold the works of the Lord, what desolations he hath made in the earth.

verses.text_plain: He maketh wars to cease unto the end of the earth; he breaketh the bow, and cutteth the spear in sunder; he burneth the chariot in the fire.
verses.verse_html: 9He maketh wars to cease unto the end of the earth; he breaketh the bow, and cutteth the spear in sunder; he burneth the chariot in the fire.

verses.text_plain: Be still, and know that I am God: I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth.
verses.verse_html: 10Be still, and know that I am God: I will be exalted among the heathen, I will be exalted in the earth.

verses.text_plain: The Lord of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.
verses.verse_html: 11The Lord of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.
